1
00:00:06,980 --> 00:00:10,100
♪I love the clarity in your eyes♪

2
00:00:10,740 --> 00:00:13,860
♪Like a shooting star across my world♪

3
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,580
♪Repeating the goodbye we never said♪

4
00:00:18,260 --> 00:00:21,540
♪Through sleepless nights♪

5
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:25,100
♪I miss the way you looked at me♪

6
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:30,260
♪Like photos freezing that summer bit by bit♪

7
00:00:30,660 --> 00:00:35,380
♪By the shore with warm winds, maybe we'll meet again♪

8
00:00:37,380 --> 00:00:41,460
[Fall in Love Again]

9
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:43,980
[Episode 5]

10
00:00:45,460 --> 00:00:46,720
As for you,

11
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:48,120
I heard about it too.

12
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:51,000
Seeing you finally move past the dark times,

13
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,640
and make a comeback,

14
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:55,400
we're really happy for you.

15
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:57,120
Mr. Li, thank you for your concern.

16
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,440
Our past collaborations were great.

17
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:03,320
I heard you're starting a new project.

18
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,310
I was wondering if there's a role for me.

19
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:09,040
That's unfortunate.

20
00:01:09,080 --> 00:01:10,520
The cast for this show

21
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:12,480
is already locked in.

22
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:14,720
How about this?

23
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:18,200
Next time, I'll definitely reach out.

24
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:19,600
Alright.

25
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:20,800
Then I'll look forward to working together again.

26
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:21,600
Sure.

27
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:22,640
Mr. Li, I'll take my leave.

28
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:29,000
She hasn't filmed anything in four years.

29
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:34,680
The public remembers her

30
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:37,240
only for cheating and divorce scandals.

31
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:39,840
She can't just come back whenever she wants.

32
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:43,320
She really doesn't know her place.

33
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:45,520
Ms. Chu.

34
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:46,600
Why are you back?

35
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,600
I forgot my bag.

36
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:51,480
Chen, walk Ms. Chu out.

37
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:52,320
No need.

38
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:56,600
Cut!

39
00:01:56,660 --> 00:01:57,760
[Be Content]

40
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:58,520
Please go on.

41
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:00,080
Director,

42
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:02,200
you know I haven't acted in a long time,

43
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,080
but...

44
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:06,120
Sounds like you already know the situation.

45
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,440
Mr. Zhang, I can expand my range.

46
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:10,400
I'm open to any kind of role.

47
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:11,840
Director,

48
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:14,040
I really need this chance to prove myself.

49
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:16,320
The market is changing fast.

50
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,720
We look at the market.

51
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:20,720
To be honest, your market value,

52
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:22,640
I don't see it at all.

53
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:24,040
Disappear for a year

54
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:28,000
and countless better newcomers will replace you.

55
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:31,000
Let alone four years away.

56
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,000
I do have a role here.

57
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:35,640
It doesn't have much screen time,

58
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:36,880
but it really tests your acting.

59
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:42,280
There are some explicit scenes.

60
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:45,000
I don't know if you can accept that.

61
00:02:47,740 --> 00:02:49,880
[Chengdu]

62
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,000
This acting path

63
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:54,080
really doesn't suit your current situation.

64
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:17,360
Older, with a bad reputation.

65
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,880
Giving you a role is already a chance.

66
00:03:46,540 --> 00:03:47,580
[Editing Syntax]

67
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:54,640
Can you stop pacing around?

68
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:56,120
You're making me dizzy.

69
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,480
Still not through?

70
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:10,600
Do you think Yang did it just to mess with you,

71
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:11,840
and gave you a fake number?

72
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,600
No way.

73
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:18,200
Probably not.

74
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:21,440
Where are you going?

75
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,840
I'm going to find her.

76
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:24,640
Find who?

77
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:29,480
Yeah,

78
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:33,600
I did say persistence works.

79
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,840
But look at the time.

80
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,400
You've got to give her some

81
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,800
personal space.

82
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:46,840
And you can't push too hard.

83
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:48,680
That'll backfire.

84
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:50,040
Right?

85
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:52,960
This is all from experience.

86
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,200
Learn from it.

87
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:56,840
Another day,

88
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:57,680
buy me a meal,

89
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:58,960
and we're even.

90
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:00,640
Don't overthink it.

91
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:06,280
Hello, who's this?

92
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:07,440
It's me.

93
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:11,200
About that producer we mentioned before.

94
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,880
He wants to meet and talk

95
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:13,880
about future collaboration.

96
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,840
But I've got something going on right now.

97
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,040
I really can't make it in time.

98
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:20,360
Can you go first and I'll come later?

99
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:23,080
It's fine. Send me the address and I'll go.

100
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:25,000
Okay.

101
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:39,200
I sent the address. Looks like a KTV.

102
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,840
If that makes you uncomfortable,

103
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:41,880
we can do it another time.

104
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:44,800
Don't worry, I know what I'm doing.

105
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:55,420
[Yang]

106
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:58,520
Yang.

107
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,920
Come on, have another drink.

108
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:02,600
One more drink.

109
00:06:03,460 --> 00:06:04,220
Just have a drink.

110
00:06:04,660 --> 00:06:05,860
Here, let me pour you one.

111
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:11,800
Stop!

112
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:15,000
Ms. Chu.

113
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:17,040
I've heard so much about you.

114
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:19,440
I hope we can work together this time.

115
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:21,840
Please, have a seat.

116
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,240
Everyone, welcome Ms. Chu!

117
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:31,400
- Welcome. - Welcome!

118
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:32,480
Welcome.

119
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:33,400
Hello, Ms. Chu.

120
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,120
Hello.

121
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,240
To be honest,

122
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,240
since your debut,

123
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:41,520
I've been following you.

124
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,920
Maybe my status was too low back then,

125
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,040
you didn't take me seriously.

126
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:45,840
No, no.

127
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:46,920
Mr. Li, please don't say that.

128
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,400
We all made it on our own

129
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:49,440
step by step.

130
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:50,600
Still, thank you.

131
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,480
I'm here today in good faith to talk business.

132
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:57,120
I like how you talk, Ms. Chu.

133
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,640
Come on, let's have a drink.

134
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:09,880
Ms. Chu,

135
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:12,080
you look way better than on TV.

136
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,040
Let's have a drink.

137
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:14,880
Thank you.

138
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:20,480
Nice tolerance.

139
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:21,280
Great tolerance!

140
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:25,320
Great tolerance, wish I'd met you sooner.

141
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,560
Come on, another one.

142
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:28,320
No, Mr. Li.

143
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:30,120
I'm here to talk business.

144
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,400
If I drink too much, we can't talk.

145
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,360
Ms. Chu,

146
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,200
you're in the wrong here.

147
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,440
In life,

148
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,240
you can't be so goal-driven.

149
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,040
I don't usually drink.

150
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,000
But today,

151
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:48,400
I really appreciate it

152
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:49,440
for giving me this opportunity.

153
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:52,120
This one's for you.

154
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,280
Nice tolerance!

155
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,880
Ms. Chu, you should eat more.

156
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,520
You're so thin it hurts to see.

157
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:18,200
Mr. Li, you've had too much.

158
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,960
Let's talk business.

159
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,880
If we're going to work together,

160
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:25,680
we should get to know each other.

161
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:28,640
You see who people are when they drink.

162
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:31,040
- Alcohol shows character. - Exactly, alcohol shows character.

163
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,720
- Ms. Chu, have a drink. – Yeah!

164
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:33,640
- Have one. – Another one!

165
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:34,320
Drink!

166
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:39,960
- Drink! – Drink!

167
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:40,640
Enough!

168
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,240
I'm here to talk business.

169
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:43,520
If you're not,

170
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:44,520
I'm leaving.

171
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,400
Ms. Chu,

172
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:51,120
don't blow things out of proportion.

173
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:54,680
The fact that we're drinking with you tonight

174
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:57,320
is us giving you a chance.

175
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,280
Giving me a chance?

176
00:08:58,520 --> 00:08:59,520
What kind of chance?

177
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,560
A chance for you to touch my thigh?

178
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:04,320
What are you talking about?

179
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:06,240
When did I touch your thigh?

180
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:07,240
Mr. Li,

181
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,840
you're a big company boss.

182
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,320
Those basic rules of doing business,

183
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:12,880
I don't think you understand them at all.

184
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,480
Touching my thigh in front of everyone.

185
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,840
Are you really that desperate?

186
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:18,120
You have no decency at all.

187
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:20,040
This so-called dinner tonight,

188
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,440
I'm sure you all know why you are here.

189
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:24,840
You're all supposed to be respected business elites.

190
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:27,080
Do you really think this is acceptable?

191
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,440
And you, Mr. Li.

192
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:30,480
I came today because you once helped Yang.

193
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,040
That's the only reason I showed up.

194
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:33,880
But I never expected you to be this kind of person.

195
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:35,840
One last thing for all of you.

196
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,520
Show some respect to women.

197
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,240
You think you can insult people and just walk away?

198
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,960
Who are you?

199
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:51,960
He's my boyfriend.

200
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:56,360
You're an actor.

201
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,480
Believe it or not, I'll expose you!

202
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,480
Expose me for what?

203
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:01,000
Playing the hero or standing up to power?

204
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:02,400
I'm telling you.

205
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:03,480
What you did to Ms. Chu,

206
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:04,880
I recorded all your malicious behavior.

207
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:07,400
Let's go.

208
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,240
Chu Jingxi!

209
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,320
Do you still want to act?

210
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:14,880
I do, but not with someone like you.

211
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:30,840
Thanks.

212
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,200
Sorry I used you as a shield just now.

213
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,200
Just a shield?

214
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:46,080
Don't overthink it, kid.

215
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,360
You're not my type.

216
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:54,920
[Garlic Skewer]

217
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:56,080
Did you really record it just now?

218
00:10:58,680 --> 00:10:59,480
I bluffed him.

219
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,680
By the way, how did you end up there?

220
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,160
Yang told me.

221
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:10,520
Well, she's really helpful.

222
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:25,080
You're already playing matchmaker for me.

223
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,600
Isn't that a bit rushed?

224
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:30,000
He just kept asking.

225
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:32,880
By the way, aren't handsome guys the best cure

226
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:34,200
for heartbreak?

227
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:35,960
Well, thanks a lot.

228
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,000
Don't mention it.

229
00:11:40,880 --> 00:11:42,120
But about Mr. Li,

230
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,920
I still owe you an apology.

231
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,760
I really didn't know he was like that.

232
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:47,280
Everything was fine before.

233
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,520
The moment I heard something happened,

234
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:49,560
I dropped everything

235
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:50,840
and came to apologize.

236
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,920
I know it's not your fault.

237
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:55,560
You're already so busy

238
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:56,720
and still worried about me.

239
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:59,160
I'm only grateful to you.

240
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,320
Why would I blame you?

241
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:00,960
I knew it.

242
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:01,720
But...

243
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,640
when it comes to men,

244
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:04,920
it can't be forced.

245
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,360
Don't worry about it for me.

246
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,120
Got it.

247
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:11,760
Feelings come first.

248
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:14,680
They say childhood sweethearts are best.

249
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:17,720
Are you still in touch with your childhood friend, Song Xiwen?

250
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,920
Handsome, mature, and rich.

251
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,600
And most importantly, he's single.

252
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,520
Hey!

253
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:27,520
Can you stop matchmaking for me?

254
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:27,720
What?

255
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:28,880
There's nothing between us...

256
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:29,340
[Song Xiwen]

257
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:33,440
Song Xiwen.

258
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:35,720
Speak of the devil.

259
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,080
Answer it!

260
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:38,560
Hello.

261
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:39,120
Xiwen.

262
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:40,160
Speaker.

263
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:40,800
Put it on speaker.

264
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:41,360
What's up?

265
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:43,440
My dear.

266
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:45,760
You finally picked up.

267
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:48,400
What's wrong?

268
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,600
You called me?

269
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:51,120
I called you?

270
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:54,200
Are you heartbroken or did you lose your mind?

271
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,520
Check your phone.

272
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:56,960
How many missed calls do you see?

273
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:02,920
Sorry.

274
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:06,080
I didn't mean it.

275
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:09,200
I was worried about you.

276
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:12,480
I'm fine, Xiwen, don't worry.

277
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,600
You've been overseas for so many years.

278
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:15,560
When are you coming back?

279
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:16,920
Don't you want this little sister anymore?

280
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:19,720
Of course I do.

281
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,280
Hearing you say that

282
00:13:21,520 --> 00:13:22,560
puts me at ease.

283
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:23,800
It seems

284
00:13:24,760 --> 00:13:25,960
you've really moved on.

285
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,720
I called to tell you

286
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:30,920
I'll be back home soon.

287
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,560
Then hurry back.

288
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:35,120
Don't forget you owe me several meals.

289
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:37,560
Still just like when we were kids.

290
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:39,720
No problem, when I'm back,

291
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:42,120
I'll treat you every day, deal?

292
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:43,720
Okay, Xiwen.

293
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,160
Let me know as soon as you're back.

294
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:46,320
Bye.

295
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:47,320
Bye-bye.

296
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:50,720
Fate!

297
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:52,160
Such an unbelievable coincidence.

298
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:55,840
Cupid, you finally showed up!

299
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:56,600
Thank you!

300
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,320
Hey, are you okay?

301
00:13:58,720 --> 00:13:59,920
He's married.

302
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,200
He was married before.

303
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:04,520
His wife passed away a couple of years ago, didn't she?

304
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:05,920
What does that have to do with me?

305
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:07,720
You think I'm some backup plan for his marriage?

306
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:10,720
No, I mean, you—him—me...

307
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,520
You...

308
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:15,720
You're hopeless, beyond saving.

309
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:56,280
♪When clouds sink into the deep sea♪

310
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:59,560
♪Ripples spread♪

311
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:02,640
♪Traces of a racing heart♪

312
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:06,120
♪Is it the sky or its reflection♪

313
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:09,600
♪I can't tell anymore♪

314
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:13,920
♪Lost in your eyes♪

315
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:19,440
♪As we draw closer♪

316
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,600
♪The space of an embrace♪

317
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,800
♪Scatters the dark♪

318
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:30,080
♪When the wind comes, raise the sails♪

319
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,360
♪And sail on♪

320
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:37,920
♪Miles ahead are no longer a dream♪

321
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:43,800
♪Where even migratory birds can't reach, you're by my side♪

322
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:49,600
♪Then I can spread my wings and fly with courage♪

323
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:55,360
♪If storms rise, I'll follow your light♪

324
00:15:56,880 --> 00:16:01,200
♪Trusting we'll reach a warm shore♪

325
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:06,960
♪Where even migratory birds can't reach, you're by my side♪

326
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:13,440
♪I'll break through the haze and run toward what I once longed for♪

327
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:18,480
♪Even if I'm hurt, I won't wander alone♪

328
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:22,880
♪You're where my heart belongs♪

